identificationRemarks: The fruit are on this years stems, the twigs seem more or less round/"terete" the plants seem low growing and the berry is glaucous so probably not *V. membranaceum*. Using Flora of the Pacific Northwest this narrows it down to *V. cespitosum* and *V. deliciosum*. I went with *V. deliciosum* because the leaves do not seem "strongly reticulate beneath" and possibly are glaucous beneath and the leaves seem large than 1-3 centimeters on average, closer to the 1.5 - 5 cm listed for *V. deliciosum*. This could of course be wrong so if anyone has ideas or objections that would be great to hear.
